$ Excel Object Model: Button
@ Button

A `button` object executes a macro when the user clicks on the button.

The `button` object is *hidden* (like, for example, the `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Global` object).

{ Adding a button and assigning a macro

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Button/add.bas||

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Button/img/add.png||

}

